window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>He’s tried everything to make the pain go away… </b><b><i>except</i></b><b> him.</b></p> <p><b>Sam</b> refuses to let his traumatising past dictate his future, so embraces life to the fullest. Stable, independent and attracted to a Guardian who’s off limits, Sam couldn’t be happier... until his father comes back from the dead.</p> <p>Facing memories he’s suppressed from childhood, and a new threat he never saw coming, Sam struggles to keep the life he’s built from crumbling.</p> <p>Cursed as a child and scarred from addiction, <b>Axel</b> never thought his life could get much worse. Until the poison that helps relieve his pain starts to affect his work, the sole reason for his existence.</p> <p>With nothing else to lose, he finally gives into his desire that he’s suppressed for so long, breaking his celibacy with the one man he's always wanted. But he quickly figures out there’s something dark lurking in the shadows, ready to test his control.</p> <p>As everything unfolds Axel must decide what’s more important, Sam's life, or his own.</p> <p><b>Dark Paranormal Romance—Friends to Lovers—Found Family—M/M—Fated Mates—Who Hurt You?</b></p> <p>---</p> <p><i>Warning: Whisper of Fate is a dark paranormal romance that contains explicit content, graphic violence, profanity, and topics that may be sensitive to some listeners. Full details can be found listed inside the book. Recommended for 18+.</i></p> <p><i>This novel is written in British English including spelling and grammar.</i></p> <p><b>Whisper of Fate can be listened to as a standalone, but recommended in order.</b></p>"; 
